	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There's also a Wolf3D port for the plain old Genesis.<br /><br />From a gamer's perspective the 32X is little else than an expensive paper weight. The few games that were made for it were mostly rubbish. But for someone who likes to develop for old video game consoles it's a pretty nice system, reminiscent of late 80s or early 90s PCs. It's also fairly easy to develop for, depending of course on how far you're trying to stretch things (theoretically you could have code running on 4 CPUs in parallel, and graphics made up of the 32X's framebuffer + the Genesis' tile layers and sprites)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


