	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've never seen the 32X in RGB, but in Composite the mixing of 32X and Genesis graphics doesn't result in any noticeable loss of quality. I really don't see why there would be any loss. I've always thought the 32X was an interesting and under utilized piece of hardware. I don't think it really had a chance in the marketplace but it's interesting to see what you could do with it. <br /><br />There was a point in time where for gamers the 32X was worth it because the 32X cost maybe $20 at most and most games weren't much more than that. There aren't alot of titles but enough for that low cost of entry to have been worth it at the time.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


